The zeros will be easier to find if we factor the polynomial.

$\qquad\begin{align}
y &= (x^2-4)(2x^3-7x^2+5x)\\\\
&= \green{(x-2)} \blue{(x+2)} (2x^3-7x^2+5x)\\\\
&= \green{(x-2)} \blue{(x+2)} \purple{x} \pink{(2x-5)} \red{(x-1)}
\end{align}$

